<$fill $name="body">

!! Can two plugins register pages at the same path?

Yes. The system uses `first[]` — the first tiddler found wins (shadow tiddler ordering is by title). Users can override by creating a non-shadow tiddler with the same tag and path.

!! How does multi-path work?

The `llm-help-path` field accepts space-separated paths. A page with `llm-help-path: a/b c/d` appears as a child of both `a` and `c`. The LLM navigates to either path and sees the same content.

!! What happens when a page has children but no content?

The tool lists the children with their descriptions. A "virtual parent" node is synthesized — no explicit tiddler needed at intermediate levels.

!! How does context filtering work?

Pages with no `llm-help-context` are always visible. Pages with `llm-help-context: rimir/appify/channels` are visible when the active context includes `rimir/appify` (or `rimir/appify/channels` exactly). Matching is hierarchical: an active context key matches any page context key that starts with it. The active context is a space-separated list of keys.

!! Can users edit or override plugin-provided help pages?

Yes. Create a regular tiddler (not shadow) with the same tag and a matching `llm-help-path`. Non-shadow tiddlers take precedence over shadow tiddlers in TiddlyWiki.

!! Why doesn't the root page use `_llm-help-at`?

The root page has an empty `llm-help-path` value. Since `enlist-input[]` on an empty string returns nothing, `_llm-help-at` can't match it. The root is found via `_llm-help-root-page` which checks for blank path directly.

